observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management ensure that the:

Collecting officers remit their collections daily to the liquidating officer in compliance with Section 88(A) of the LTOM, 2nd Edition;

Liquidating officer strictly monitor the daily remittance of the collecting officers;

AFC strictly update the CRAAF with the individual RAAF of the collecting officers to monitor and readily detect any unremitted collections from accountable forms; and

AFC issue additional accountable forms to collecting officers only upon remittance of collections to avoid accumulation of cash in the custody of collecting officers, all in compliance with the rules and regulations concerning receipts of collections.

We recommended that the Management, through the concerned offices, undertake the following actions to facilitate fair presentation of accounts presented in the financial statements by:
ensuring that all procurements are recorded under the appropriate inventory accounts reflecting accurately their intended use;
promptly submitting supporting documents for distributed inventories to ensure that expenses are recorded in the correct period;
reconciling the unrecorded inventory utilization and make the necessary adjustments in the City’s books; and
conducting physical inventory counts to verify recorded balances and promptly adjust any discrepancies.

We recommended that Management:

Require the City Treasurer’s Office and City Accounting Office to review the Schedule of National Collection – Bureau of Treasury and include only the amounts that are classified under “Building Fees and Other Charges” account;

Require the City Accounting Office to maintain a trust fund for the said account in compliance with Item 2.1 of DPWH – DILG JMC No. 001 dated July 4, 2013;

Require the City Treasurer’s Office to account the five (5) percent share of the DPWH and remit the total amount to DPWH Secretary thru the Bureau of Treasury under Special Account No. 154 in compliance with Item 2.3 of the same JMC and Section 208 of PD No. 1096 dated February 19, 1977.  Thereafter, immediately notify the DPWH Secretary thru the National Building Code Development Office that its 5 percent share has already been remitted to his account in compliance with Item 2.5 of the same JMC; and

Require the Office of Building Official to prepare a Program of Work detailing how it would utilize the 15 percent share to be approved by the Local Chief Executive and thereafter submit a copy of the duly approved Program of Work to the DPWH Secretary thru the National Building Code Development Office (NCBDO) in compliance with Items 2.6 and 2.7, respectively of the same JMC.

